<p><strong>Calatagan, Batangas</strong> is one of the most rewarding day-trip destinations from Metro Manila — a coastal municipality at the southwestern tip of Batangas province, facing the South China Sea. Here's your complete guide.</p>

<h2>Why Visit Calatagan?</h2>
<p>Calatagan offers something increasingly rare for travelers from Manila: a genuinely natural, uncrowded coastal experience within driving distance. The municipality is home to several notable attractions including <strong>Little Boracay sandbar</strong>, the <strong>Starfish Sandbar</strong>, CaSoBe beach, and Stilts Resort — all easily combined into a full-day itinerary.</p>

<h2>Top Attractions in Calatagan, Batangas</h2>

<h3>1. Little Boracay Sandbar</h3>
<p>The most iconic destination in Calatagan. A natural tidal sandbar with turquoise-clear shallow water, white sand, and iconic floating bamboo cottages. The signature experience — see our <a href="/sandbar">sandbar guide</a> and <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a>.</p>

<h3>2. Starfish Sandbar</h3>
<p>A magical shallow coastal area where live starfish are visible in crystal-clear water. Often combined with Little Boracay as part of a <a href="/blog/starfish-sandbar-calatagan">combo day tour</a>.</p>

<h3>3. CaSoBe (Calatagan South Beach)</h3>
<p>A beach resort area along the south coast of Calatagan offering accommodation, day access, and beach facilities for groups and families.</p>

<h3>4. Stilts Beach Resort</h3>
<p>Known for over-water villas built on stilts — a popular option for overnight stays and special occasions in Calatagan.</p>

<h2>How to Get to Calatagan from Manila</h2>
<p>Drive south via SLEX then STAR Tollway, exit toward Lian, Batangas, and follow roads to Calatagan. Drive time is 3–4 hours. Full directions in our <a href="/blog/how-to-get-to-little-boracay-from-manila">Manila to Little Boracay travel guide</a>.</p>

<h2>Best Time to Visit Calatagan</h2>
<p>November to May (dry season) is ideal. December through April is peak season. See our <a href="/blog/best-time-to-visit-little-boracay">full timing guide</a>.</p>

